A 78-year-old pensioner, Dick Johannes Hattingh, was found guilty by Nelspruit Magistrates&#8217; Court on Wednesday on 12 counts of theft. Directorate for Priority Crime Investigation (Hawks) spokesperson Captain Dineo Lucy Sekgotodi on Friday said: In November 2015, the accused was employed at Lowveld Hunting Club, and he stole R527 000 from the Club. Sekgotodi said a custodial sentence was postponed for five years on condition that Hattingh paid back the money in monthly installments of R3 000 over five years.